1
00:00:49,762 --> 00:00:51,558
CITY OF GOD

2
00:01:52,590 --> 00:01:58,358
Fuck, the chicken's got away!
Go after that chicken, man!

3
00:02:00,966 --> 00:02:03,161
Go on, for fuck's sake!

4
00:02:07,272 --> 00:02:09,400
Get that chicken!

5
00:02:23,355 --> 00:02:26,051
If it’s a good photo,
I'll get a job at the paper.

6
00:02:26,258 --> 00:02:28,419
-You think so, Rocket?
-Gotta take the risk.

7
00:02:28,627 --> 00:02:33,257
You'd risk your life
for a picture? Forget it!

8
00:02:33,832 --> 00:02:37,165
You think I want to meet up
with that motherfucking hood?

9
00:02:38,204 --> 00:02:42,072
Get that chicken, bro!

10
00:02:44,342 --> 00:02:47,368
Motherfucker! I told you
to grab that chicken!

11
00:02:47,580 --> 00:02:49,707
Outta my way!

12
00:02:49,949 --> 00:02:51,917
Get that chicken!

13
00:03:11,537 --> 00:03:13,266
If Li’l Z' catches you,
he'll kill you.

14
00:03:15,140 --> 00:03:17,905
Yeah, well,
he's gotta find me first.

15
00:03:26,852 --> 00:03:30,480
Hey, kid! Get that chicken!
Get that chicken!

16
00:03:33,025 --> 00:03:34,355
Shit! The cops!

17
00:03:34,560 --> 00:03:36,824
Don't fucking run off!

18
00:03:37,028 --> 00:03:38,825
Give me that.

19
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:43,901
Hey, Melonhead! You fucking fag!

20
00:03:44,969 --> 00:03:47,461
A picture could change
my life, but...

21
00:03:47,673 --> 00:03:50,937
in the City of God, if you
run away, they get you...

22
00:03:51,544 --> 00:03:55,002
...and if you stay, they get you too.
-They’re coming for us!

23
00:03:55,213 --> 00:03:57,876
It's been that way
ever since I was a kid...

24
00:04:00,618 --> 00:04:04,520
THE SIXTIES

25
00:04:11,463 --> 00:04:12,862
You’re useless, man!

26
00:04:13,064 --> 00:04:15,897
-Go get the ball!
-Fucking useless!

27
00:04:19,004 --> 00:04:20,198
Hey, kid!

28
00:04:20,406 --> 00:04:23,432
Give me the ball, I wanna play.

29
00:04:25,244 --> 00:04:28,771
-It’s not yours.
-You wanna mess with me?

30
00:04:28,980 --> 00:04:31,415
Fuck off.

31
00:04:31,617 --> 00:04:35,781
-What’s your name?
-Sorry, I forgot to introduce myself.

32
00:04:35,987 --> 00:04:38,512
-My name’s Rocket.
-Some advice, Rocket...

33
00:04:39,125 --> 00:04:42,288
Don’t let Li’l Dice
touch that ball. He sucks.

34
00:04:42,795 --> 00:04:44,786
-You lose, pal.
-Go, Shaggy!

35
00:04:44,997 --> 00:04:47,227
That's Shaggy.

36
00:04:47,432 --> 00:04:50,834
To tell the story of the City of God,
I have to start with him.

37
00:04:51,036 --> 00:04:53,060
8, 9, 10, 11...

38
00:04:54,339 --> 00:04:58,742
But in order to tell Shaggy's story, I
must tell the story of the Tender Trio.

39
00:04:58,944 --> 00:05:03,141
Well, Shaggy? The gas truck’s coming.
What are you fucking around for?

40
00:05:03,348 --> 00:05:05,283
You’re not gonna chicken out...

41
00:05:08,620 --> 00:05:12,147
THE STORY OF THE TENDER TRIO

42
00:05:17,829 --> 00:05:21,288
The notorious Tender Trio
was legendary in the City of God.

43
00:05:21,500 --> 00:05:23,057
Shaggy...

44
00:05:23,769 --> 00:05:25,430
Clipper...

45
00:05:26,105 --> 00:05:27,572
and Goose.

46
00:05:29,507 --> 00:05:33,238
Tagging along were always
Li’l Dice and Benny...

47
00:05:33,444 --> 00:05:35,379
Shaggy's brother.

48
00:05:36,649 --> 00:05:40,312
I never had the courage
to follow my brother, Goose.

49
00:05:48,894 --> 00:05:50,862
Okay, let’s go.

50
00:05:51,529 --> 00:05:53,656
Come on, Goose.

51
00:05:53,932 --> 00:05:55,423
Let’s go!

52
00:06:05,411 --> 00:06:07,379
Stop! Stop!
Stop this fucker!

53
00:06:12,151 --> 00:06:15,985
Stop or I’ll shoot, motherfucker!

54
00:06:16,187 --> 00:06:18,485
Get out!

55
00:06:18,891 --> 00:06:23,954
Hurry up, asshole!
Gimme the money!

56
00:06:24,230 --> 00:06:26,824
Who wants gas?

57
00:06:35,406 --> 00:06:38,933
More! You wanna die for your
boss’ damn money?

58
00:06:39,144 --> 00:06:41,134
Shitloads of money here!

59
00:06:43,281 --> 00:06:45,579
You see, asshole?

60
00:06:46,584 --> 00:06:47,745
Asshole!

61
00:06:47,952 --> 00:06:49,920
Fuck! The cops!

62
00:06:53,259 --> 00:06:55,352
Let’s get outta here!

63
00:06:59,398 --> 00:07:03,129
Clear out! The place is
crawling with cops!

64
00:07:18,916 --> 00:07:22,147
-Shaggy!
-The ball, Goose, it’s yours!

65
00:07:32,064 --> 00:07:34,692
Back then, I thought
the guys in the Tender Trio...

66
00:07:34,899 --> 00:07:37,060
were the most dangerous hoods
in Rio.

67
00:07:37,269 --> 00:07:40,704
Here! Buy some new balls.

68
00:07:42,307 --> 00:07:45,709
But they were just amateurs.

69
00:07:48,579 --> 00:07:52,572
-Even my brother, Goose.
-Rocket, give this money to dad.

70
00:07:54,720 --> 00:07:57,052
But don’t tell him it’s from me.

71
00:07:57,255 --> 00:07:59,485
Okay?

72
00:07:59,692 --> 00:08:02,684
-Hey, Stringy!
-Yeah?

73
00:08:02,894 --> 00:08:05,158
Look how much I’ve got.

74
00:08:20,646 --> 00:08:25,379
We came to the City of God
hoping to find paradise.

75
00:08:25,584 --> 00:08:30,247
Many families were homeless
due to flooding...

76
00:08:30,456 --> 00:08:32,855
and acts of arson
in the ghettos.

77
00:08:33,057 --> 00:08:35,992
-A light post!
-We’ll have electricity!

78
00:08:36,195 --> 00:08:38,355
The bigwigs in government
didn't joke around.

79
00:08:38,563 --> 00:08:41,498
Homeless? Off to City of God!

80
00:08:41,700 --> 00:08:45,761
There was no electricity,
paved streets or transportation.

81
00:08:45,971 --> 00:08:49,168
But for the rich and powerful
our problems didn't matter.

82
00:08:49,408 --> 00:08:52,377
We were too far removed...

83
00:08:52,577 --> 00:08:55,045
from the picture postcard image
of Rio de Janeiro.

84
00:09:11,764 --> 00:09:14,494
Do you think I can become
a lifeguard one day?

85
00:09:14,700 --> 00:09:16,531
I don’t know.

86
00:09:16,735 --> 00:09:19,601
Being a lifeguard is better
than a fishmonger.

87
00:09:19,804 --> 00:09:22,329
I don’t want to sell fish.
It stinks.

88
00:09:22,875 --> 00:09:25,240
-Are you insulting your father?
-No.

89
00:09:25,977 --> 00:09:28,947
So what do you want to be?

90
00:09:29,347 --> 00:09:30,974
I don’t know.

91
00:09:31,250 --> 00:09:34,777
-Not a hood or a policeman.
-Why not?

92
00:09:34,986 --> 00:09:37,147
I’m scared of getting shot.

93
00:09:41,626 --> 00:09:44,094
Put that thing away, kid.
Are you nuts?

94
00:09:44,296 --> 00:09:47,788
Pointing that gun at me?

95
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:51,230
Take it easy with the kid, Goose.
Li’l Dice is with me.

96
00:09:51,437 --> 00:09:54,269
Right, I'm a gangster too.

97
00:09:54,472 --> 00:09:57,100
-That gas truck didn't bring much.
-So what?

98
00:09:57,308 --> 00:10:00,937
-We rob gas trucks every day.
-One today, another tomorrow.

99
00:10:01,279 --> 00:10:03,440
No, we need to rob
some rich guy’s house.

100
00:10:03,649 --> 00:10:06,082
That’s the only
way to get outta here.

101
00:10:06,284 --> 00:10:09,583
Hell, no. What you need
is to follow my plan.

102
00:10:09,788 --> 00:10:11,221
That’s it.

103
00:10:11,423 --> 00:10:15,519
The little fart’s getting
too big for his britches!

104
00:10:21,466 --> 00:10:24,833
He gets high and starts
talking bullshit.

105
00:10:25,037 --> 00:10:30,201
You two junkies aren't worth
half as much as that kid.

106
00:10:32,009 --> 00:10:35,069
What you got in mind, Li’l Dice?

107
00:10:35,279 --> 00:10:39,875
To be a real hood you need
more than just a gun. You need ideas.

108
00:10:43,087 --> 00:10:45,180
And Li’l Dice had them.

109
00:10:46,357 --> 00:10:48,848
-Is that the motel?
-Yeah.

110
00:10:49,260 --> 00:10:53,993
We go in, grab the money and
get out. No killing, got that?

111
00:10:54,198 --> 00:10:57,531
-I need this.
-Don’t touch my gun, kid.

112
00:10:57,735 --> 00:10:58,929
Don’t ever do that again.

113
00:10:59,136 --> 00:11:00,728
-Don’t point at me.
-Fuck you.

114
00:11:00,938 --> 00:11:04,601
-Don’t point your finger at me!
-Stop acting like a baby!

115
00:11:05,309 --> 00:11:06,503
Here’s yours.

116
00:11:06,711 --> 00:11:09,111
-Awesome!
-Let’s go!

117
00:11:09,313 --> 00:11:11,838
-Not so fast!
-What?

118
00:11:12,049 --> 00:11:14,517
You stay here and keep watch.

119
00:11:14,785 --> 00:11:20,087
If the cops come, shoot that
window over there.

120
00:11:20,292 --> 00:11:23,192
-Why me? Let that dork do that.
-Look...

121
00:11:23,394 --> 00:11:28,593
I gave you this great plan, for free...
While that guy’s absolutely useless!

122
00:11:28,799 --> 00:11:30,562
-You just had the idea.
-Exactly!

123
00:11:30,769 --> 00:11:33,259
You’re just a kid, remember?

124
00:11:33,871 --> 00:11:36,601
You cover us, okay?

125
00:11:37,609 --> 00:11:42,376
You’ll get your turn, so cool it.
Stop trying to rush things.

126
00:11:42,581 --> 00:11:45,072
You stay there.

127
00:11:48,886 --> 00:11:52,014
This is a hold-up, bitch.

128
00:11:55,126 --> 00:12:01,793
You should be studying or working.
You don't even look like hoodlums.

129
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:05,993
Instead, you ought to be
working or studying, boy.

130
00:12:06,203 --> 00:12:09,070
Shut up!
What a pain in the ass!

131
00:12:10,042 --> 00:12:11,805
Okay, Clipper?

132
00:12:13,845 --> 00:12:15,244
Shall we go in?

133
00:12:20,586 --> 00:12:22,850
I didn't order anything.

134
00:12:23,054 --> 00:12:27,184
It’s on the house, sir.
Hand over the money!

135
00:12:27,392 --> 00:12:29,656
Keep calm, all I want
is your cash.

136
00:12:29,860 --> 00:12:31,452
-Don’t point that...
-Your wallet...

137
00:12:43,875 --> 00:12:45,399
Hey, man...

138
00:12:45,610 --> 00:12:47,806
What kind of whorehouse is this?

139
00:12:51,048 --> 00:12:53,608
-You from the church?
-Yes, brother.

140
00:12:56,687 --> 00:12:57,677
Give it to me!

141
00:12:59,890 --> 00:13:01,187
Slut!

142
00:13:01,426 --> 00:13:03,223
You're old, fat and flabby!

143
00:13:04,196 --> 00:13:06,494
Wanna take her place?

144
00:13:10,969 --> 00:13:13,129
What’s going on?

145
00:13:14,272 --> 00:13:16,968
-The cops! Let’s beat it!
-Let’s go!

146
00:13:22,114 --> 00:13:25,605
Take that car.
I'll go get Li’l Dice.

147
00:13:26,985 --> 00:13:29,418
Jesus, what a car!

148
00:13:35,360 --> 00:13:40,161
-Something fucked up. Li’l Dice’s gone.
-The cops are shooting, let’s go!

149
00:14:07,192 --> 00:14:09,591
Slow down! Hold on...

150
00:14:09,794 --> 00:14:12,627
-You said you knew how to drive.
-I do, so cool it!

151
00:14:12,831 --> 00:14:15,527
Turn! Watch out!

152
00:14:29,147 --> 00:14:30,910
You fucking asshole!

153
00:14:31,982 --> 00:14:34,678
Hey, I didn’t do it on purpose.

154
00:14:34,885 --> 00:14:38,514
No one saw anything.
So keep your mouths shut, understand?

155
00:14:42,293 --> 00:14:45,194
Hold on, I twisted my ankle.

156
00:14:45,397 --> 00:14:47,729
Goose fucked up his ankle.

157
00:14:47,932 --> 00:14:48,922
It fucking hurts.

158
00:14:49,134 --> 00:14:53,036
Take him into the woods.
I’ll shoot to distract the cops.

159
00:14:53,238 --> 00:14:55,570
-In God we trust.
-In God we trust.

160
00:15:00,479 --> 00:15:02,743
Pass me the telephone, Penguin.

161
00:15:02,947 --> 00:15:06,850
Shorty is another notorious guy
in the City of God.

162
00:15:07,052 --> 00:15:09,076
But it's not yet time
to tell his story.

163
00:15:10,955 --> 00:15:14,982
-It fucking hurts, Goose.
-Shut up.

164
00:15:15,693 --> 00:15:20,426
-Wait up...
-You sound like a damn sissy, man.

165
00:15:24,501 --> 00:15:27,766
-Give me your hand! Climb up!
-No one saw anything?

166
00:15:27,971 --> 00:15:32,807
How odd! A car crashes
into a bar and no one saw a thing.

167
00:15:33,010 --> 00:15:36,002
I suppose you didn’t see
anything either?

168
00:15:36,214 --> 00:15:39,945
As usual, no one saw,
no one knows.

169
00:15:40,684 --> 00:15:44,142
So what’s up, Shorty?

170
00:15:44,822 --> 00:15:47,586
They’re hiding in the woods.

171
00:15:48,592 --> 00:15:50,253
-Hello, Melonhead.
-How are you doing?

172
00:15:50,461 --> 00:15:53,898
I have this feeling that
they’re out in the woods.

173
00:15:54,131 --> 00:15:57,692
-The motherfuckers.
-They’re out in the woods.

174
00:15:58,470 --> 00:16:01,633
Felipe, lock up the car.
Rangel, come with me.

175
00:16:06,043 --> 00:16:09,308
I can’t see a thing.
How the hell can they see?

176
00:16:09,514 --> 00:16:11,947
Fucking jungle.

177
00:16:16,221 --> 00:16:20,282
-They stole a fortune at that motel.
-I know.

178
00:16:22,626 --> 00:16:25,288
What if we took the money?

179
00:16:25,797 --> 00:16:29,961
Are you crazy?
I’m not getting mixed up in that.

180
00:16:30,168 --> 00:16:32,727
I want to exterminate these guys.

181
00:16:32,937 --> 00:16:37,236
What? Since when is stealing from
niggers and thieves a crime?

182
00:16:37,575 --> 00:16:44,242
It won't be hard to nab them.
I have a stoolie in the City.

183
00:17:09,106 --> 00:17:15,773
-Did you hear those shots?
-If I catch one of them, I'll kill him.

184
00:17:27,525 --> 00:17:29,048
Maracana!

185
00:17:29,359 --> 00:17:31,554
Open the door.

186
00:17:33,832 --> 00:17:37,563
-What’s the matter?
-The cops are after me.

187
00:17:45,943 --> 00:17:47,342
Shaggy!

188
00:17:48,546 --> 00:17:51,413
-Shaggy!
-The cops are on my ass!

189
00:17:51,615 --> 00:17:54,846
-Hide me!
-Quick, come in.

190
00:18:02,693 --> 00:18:07,028
Shit... I thought the cops
would be down there all night.

191
00:18:08,365 --> 00:18:11,267
I had a vision, Goose.

192
00:18:12,002 --> 00:18:14,732
You been smoking something?

193
00:18:15,073 --> 00:18:17,906
-You've had a job, right?
-Yeah.

194
00:18:18,108 --> 00:18:20,167
What’s it like?
What do people say?

195
00:18:20,377 --> 00:18:22,504
I worked with my father.

196
00:18:22,713 --> 00:18:26,274
And fathers talk a lot of shit.

197
00:18:27,518 --> 00:18:31,545
You know what, Goose?
I'm getting out, I don't want to die.

198
00:18:31,756 --> 00:18:37,160
-This gangster’s life isn’t for me.
-Wait! The cops are still down there.

199
00:18:37,362 --> 00:18:40,024
I don’t give a shit.

200
00:18:42,200 --> 00:18:44,862
I'm going back to the church.

201
00:18:45,470 --> 00:18:47,563
He that dwells in the secret
place of the most High...

202
00:18:47,771 --> 00:18:51,138
shall abide under the shadow of
the Almighty. I will say of the Lord...

203
00:18:51,342 --> 00:18:55,608
He is my refuge and my fortress,
in Him will I trust.

204
00:18:55,813 --> 00:18:59,044
Fear not the terror by night,
nor the arrow that flies by day...

205
00:18:59,250 --> 00:19:03,277
nor the pestilence that walks
in darkness, nor the destruction...

206
00:19:03,488 --> 00:19:07,355
-Stop, motherfucker!
-Don’t move!

207
00:19:07,692 --> 00:19:11,127
Stop, or I’ll shoot!

208
00:19:12,763 --> 00:19:17,791
...shall abide under the shadow
of the Almighty.

209
00:19:18,001 --> 00:19:22,769
The hold-up at the motel went down
as the bloodiest in history.

210
00:19:22,973 --> 00:19:25,807
The destinies of the outlaws
then took different paths.

211
00:19:26,009 --> 00:19:29,445
I don’t think this guy
was involved in the heist.

212
00:19:29,646 --> 00:19:31,341
See here?

213
00:19:31,548 --> 00:19:36,952
-He’s a worker, not a hoodlum.
-I’ll make him one now.

214
00:19:40,223 --> 00:19:44,523
Destiny put Clipper
back into the hands of God.

215
00:19:46,064 --> 00:19:50,228
Shaggy was in Bernice's hands.

216
00:19:51,868 --> 00:19:55,395
And Goose was
in my father's hands.

217
00:19:55,605 --> 00:19:59,097
Why do you do these things?
You think I’m a fool?

218
00:19:59,309 --> 00:20:02,005
From now on,
you’ll work with me.

219
00:20:02,212 --> 00:20:06,376
Your younger brother
will keep an eye on you.

220
00:20:06,584 --> 00:20:08,575
You listen to me.

221
00:20:08,786 --> 00:20:13,154
If I catch you with money that
isn't yours, I'll kill you.

222
00:20:13,357 --> 00:20:19,227
That goes for you too. Get changed!
You start work immediately.

223
00:20:19,430 --> 00:20:25,198
Having a hood as a brother sucks.
You always end up footing the bill.

224
00:20:25,403 --> 00:20:29,669
Don’t worry.
Dad’s mad at me...

225
00:20:29,874 --> 00:20:34,277
but he’ll get over it.

226
00:20:37,414 --> 00:20:41,475
Give me that, Rocket. It’s not
for you. You have to study.

227
00:20:41,685 --> 00:20:45,019
-Getting shot doesn’t scare you?
-I’m a hood because I got no brain.

228
00:20:45,222 --> 00:20:49,057
But you’re smart.
You should study.

229
00:20:49,559 --> 00:20:52,858
I go to school because
I don’t like physical work.

230
00:20:53,397 --> 00:20:57,993
Promise me something... That you’ll
never touch this gun. Promise?

231
00:20:58,736 --> 00:21:00,795
Let’s shake.

232
00:21:02,306 --> 00:21:04,865
We’d better hurry.

233
00:21:06,144 --> 00:21:09,671
I’m gonna sell a lot of fish.
And don’t laugh.

234
00:21:09,881 --> 00:21:11,644
You grinned when I got slapped.

235
00:21:11,848 --> 00:21:13,749
-Who, me?
-I saw you.

236
00:21:41,711 --> 00:21:45,203
What is it, Shaggy?
Cat got your tongue?

237
00:21:45,415 --> 00:21:48,009
Your fidgeting behind me
makes me nervous.

238
00:21:48,219 --> 00:21:52,383
-I'm thinking of what to say to you.
-You’re thinking, as well?

239
00:21:52,589 --> 00:21:54,922
