From Shaggy. You'll need it.

473
00:42:31,925 --> 00:42:34,554
From one hit to the next,
Li’l Dice grew up.

474
00:42:34,762 --> 00:42:39,164
At 18, he was the most
respected hood in the City of God.

475
00:42:39,367 --> 00:42:41,426
You’re of age now, watch out!

476
00:42:41,635 --> 00:42:44,934
He was one of the most
wanted robbers in Rio.

477
00:42:58,219 --> 00:42:59,880
Li’l Dice, how’s it going?

478
00:43:00,088 --> 00:43:03,717
Happy birthday.
I’m so glad you’ve turned 18...

479
00:43:03,925 --> 00:43:07,156
-Get lost, Tuba!
-Excuse me, amigo...

480
00:43:07,795 --> 00:43:09,854
Give me a beer!

481
00:43:10,063 --> 00:43:13,692
Didn’t you see me, prick?

482
00:43:13,900 --> 00:43:15,765
-Sorry, man.
-Up yours!

483
00:43:15,969 --> 00:43:19,336
The next time,
I’ll waste you, asshole!

484
00:43:20,742 --> 00:43:22,767
Fag!

485
00:43:23,110 --> 00:43:26,045
Li'l Dice was ready for anything.

486
00:43:26,246 --> 00:43:28,181
I wanna talk.

487
00:43:28,382 --> 00:43:31,374
-And he was itching to start.
-Who are the fattest cats here?

488
00:43:31,818 --> 00:43:36,050
-There are tons of them.
-Look at Jerry Adriani...

489
00:43:36,257 --> 00:43:40,353
gold chain, snazzy clothes.

490
00:43:40,561 --> 00:43:42,756
Look at Pereira
and the chick he’s with...

491
00:43:42,963 --> 00:43:46,831
-Bernice. She was my brother’s girl.
-Check out his car.

492
00:43:47,434 --> 00:43:51,565
Then there’s Blacky.
Covered in gold.

493
00:43:51,773 --> 00:43:54,434
Gold chain, gold watch...

494
00:43:54,641 --> 00:43:57,804
Look at Carrot, and his car.

495
00:43:58,012 --> 00:44:01,743
-They’re all dealers.
-They’re all fucking loaded.

496
00:44:01,949 --> 00:44:03,974
Hold-ups bring in chickenshit.

497
00:44:04,184 --> 00:44:06,982
-The big bucks are in drugs.
-I see.

498
00:44:07,188 --> 00:44:09,179
Especially in selling coke.

499
00:44:09,389 --> 00:44:11,653
-But you need money.
-Not really...

500
00:44:11,858 --> 00:44:15,556
We’ll kill these clowns
and take over their business.

501
00:44:15,762 --> 00:44:18,527
-When do we start?
-Now.

502
00:44:28,041 --> 00:44:32,999
Exu-the-Devil is the light
that shines forth.

503
00:44:32,213 --> 00:44:34,807
He brought you here.

504
00:44:35,016 --> 00:44:40,215
Why remain in the City of God
where God has forgotten you?

505
00:44:41,088 --> 00:44:45,490
I know what you want.
You want power.

506
00:44:45,693 --> 00:44:49,823
I have something which will
give it to you.

507
00:44:51,364 --> 00:44:55,858
To change your fate,
I give you my protector, boy.

508
00:44:56,070 --> 00:44:59,664
But you mustn't fornicate
with the amulet...

509
00:44:59,873 --> 00:45:02,341
otherwise...

510
00:45:03,411 --> 00:45:05,811
you’ll die.

511
00:45:06,313 --> 00:45:08,713
The boy is no longer called
Li’l Dice...

512
00:45:08,916 --> 00:45:10,907
but Li’l Z’.

513
00:45:11,117 --> 00:45:14,679
Li’l Z’ will grow up.

514
00:45:14,989 --> 00:45:18,789
You stick with me,
I’ll stick with you.

515
00:45:30,070 --> 00:45:33,528
Li’l Dice became Li'l Z'
and he began to kill.

516
00:45:34,574 --> 00:45:41,241
He started one morning,
taking over Jerry Adriani's racket.

517
00:45:42,449 --> 00:45:46,818
By that night, almost all
of the rackets in the ghetto were his.

518
00:45:47,021 --> 00:45:50,422
The only business he didn't
touch was Carrot's...

519
00:45:50,625 --> 00:45:54,583
since he was a friend of Benny's.
All that was left was the apartment...

520
00:45:54,795 --> 00:45:55,853
But that would be easy.

521
00:46:00,635 --> 00:46:03,695
Who is it?

522
00:46:10,443 --> 00:46:12,308
-Hey, Blacky.
-Fuck, Li’l Dice.

523
00:46:12,512 --> 00:46:18,644
-You show up like this at my place?
-Who said it was your place?

524
00:46:18,853 --> 00:46:20,480
-Something wrong, Li’l Dice?
-Li’l Dice, my ass.

525
00:46:20,688 --> 00:46:24,146
-My name is Li’l Z’ now.
-His name’s Li’l Z’, see?

526
00:46:24,358 --> 00:46:27,486
-You’re a goner, bastard.
-Don’t kill him. He understands.

527
00:46:27,695 --> 00:46:29,822
Right, Blacky?

528
00:46:30,030 --> 00:46:34,558
It’s all yours, I don’t want anything.
I don’t want no trouble, okay?

529
00:46:34,768 --> 00:46:37,896
I should have taken this chance
to avenge my brother's death.

530
00:46:39,773 --> 00:46:44,472
You’ll live, but you’ll
work for us. Understand?

531
00:46:44,679 --> 00:46:46,771
That's easy to say...

532
00:46:48,114 --> 00:46:51,311
-Where are you going?
-He’s clean, Li’l Z’.

533
00:46:51,885 --> 00:46:53,318
What’s your name, kid?

534
00:46:53,521 --> 00:46:57,321
-Rocket.
-He’s Goose’s brother.

535
00:46:57,525 --> 00:47:00,119
-Goose?
-The late Goose.

536
00:47:01,329 --> 00:47:03,593
Quick, kid. Run along.

537
00:47:03,797 --> 00:47:08,257
Tell everyone that this business
now belongs to Li’l Z’.

538
00:47:08,469 --> 00:47:12,371
And that we'll be selling coke.
Got that?

539
00:47:12,739 --> 00:47:14,468
Cocaine.

540
00:47:17,478 --> 00:47:20,413
-Where’s the turf?
-Over there, on the left.

541
00:47:20,614 --> 00:47:23,639
Selling drugs is like any
other business.

542
00:47:23,985 --> 00:47:25,885
The supplier
delivers the merchandise...

543
00:47:26,086 --> 00:47:28,817
which is then
packaged on the premises.

544
00:47:29,155 --> 00:47:32,956
It's done in an assembly line.

545
00:47:33,159 --> 00:47:35,219
Boring as hell...

546
00:47:35,695 --> 00:47:39,722
Pot is wrapped up in "lids".

547
00:47:40,001 --> 00:47:42,697
Cocaine is put into packets...

548
00:47:43,436 --> 00:47:47,668
and then into bundles
of 10 or 100.

549
00:47:48,041 --> 00:47:50,909
You can even make a career
in dealing drugs.

550
00:47:51,112 --> 00:47:54,945
The kids start out
as delivery boys.

551
00:47:55,215 --> 00:47:59,208
They're paid to run errands
and take messages.

552
00:47:59,954 --> 00:48:02,946
Then they become lookouts.
If the police arrive...

553
00:48:03,157 --> 00:48:05,990
the kites disappear
and everyone scrams.

554
00:48:07,260 --> 00:48:10,855
Later, you become a dealer
or a "vapor".

555
00:48:11,065 --> 00:48:14,159
When the heat's on, the
"vapor" quickly evaporates.

556
00:48:14,367 --> 00:48:18,498
Moving up the ladder,
you have the "soldier".

557
00:48:18,739 --> 00:48:22,333
And if the guy is good at math,
he can become a manager...

558
00:48:22,543 --> 00:48:26,001
the boss' right-hand man.

559
00:48:27,447 --> 00:48:31,384
The police receive their part
and don’t make trouble.

560
00:48:33,586 --> 00:48:36,181
Since Li’l Z' killed off
all of his enemies...

561
00:48:36,389 --> 00:48:41,349
there were no shoot-outs in the
City of God. You could drive there...

562
00:48:41,728 --> 00:48:45,255
The playboys felt safe
buying their drugs there.

563
00:48:46,699 --> 00:48:51,364
The City teemed with addicts
and Li’l Z' grew rich.

564
00:48:52,306 --> 00:48:54,603
-Is it okay?
-It’s a deal.

565
00:48:58,278 --> 00:49:02,306
-I can’t decide which to wear.
-This one’s cool.

566
00:49:03,150 --> 00:49:07,519
If dealing were legal, Li’l Z'
would have been man of the year.

567
00:49:10,791 --> 00:49:13,726
But things were risky for me.
I was afraid of him.

568
00:49:13,927 --> 00:49:18,125
-And he was everywhere.
-What a drag this guy is.

569
00:49:18,331 --> 00:49:23,462
Whenever I wanted to smoke a joint
I had to go see Carrot.

570
00:49:28,074 --> 00:49:30,975
Half a lid. Thanks.

571
00:49:32,112 --> 00:49:36,277
But it was worth it.
I only smoked with Angelica.

572
00:49:37,952 --> 00:49:40,819
She and Thiago had split up,
so I made my move.

573
00:49:41,021 --> 00:49:46,823
-I was about to win her over...
-These pictures are really great.

574
00:49:47,027 --> 00:49:50,621
-You think so?
-I look good here.

575
00:49:50,831 --> 00:49:53,595
-You look beautiful everywhere.
-I’m serious.

576
00:49:53,800 --> 00:49:54,789
Me too.

577
00:49:57,704 --> 00:50:02,938
A setting sun,
a deserted beach... a long kiss...

578
00:50:03,143 --> 00:50:05,976
I was sure this was it...

579
00:50:06,679 --> 00:50:09,170
But the Runts arrived.

580
00:50:09,750 --> 00:50:13,014
Can I have a toke?

581
00:50:18,592 --> 00:50:19,786
Here.

582
00:50:19,994 --> 00:50:24,192
I’m going. See you later.

583
00:50:26,065 --> 00:50:29,364
Hold on, Angelica.

584
00:50:29,570 --> 00:50:32,061
-Your joint, man.
-Keep it.

585
00:50:32,273 --> 00:50:34,605
What a cool guy.

586
00:50:37,577 --> 00:50:41,947
That was my first run
in with the Runts.

587
00:50:47,820 --> 00:50:50,880
-Steak and fries, Benny.
-Great! Here...

588
00:50:54,393 --> 00:51:00,332
-A tip for you.
-Really? Thanks.

589
00:51:00,532 --> 00:51:02,830
-Wanna eat something?
-No.

590
00:51:06,039 --> 00:51:10,237
-Wanna trade this watch?
-After Angelica left him...

591
00:51:10,443 --> 00:51:12,343
Thiago began snorting
more and more.

592
00:51:12,545 --> 00:51:15,639
-Is it your grandfather’s?
-No, my dad’s.

593
00:51:15,847 --> 00:51:20,148
When a guy is really hooked
he ends up in the hands of the dealer.

594
00:51:20,353 --> 00:51:22,480
-Two bags of ten.
-One of ten.

595
00:51:22,688 --> 00:51:26,784
-Okay, one bag.
-For Thiago, it was different.

596
00:51:26,992 --> 00:51:30,485
-Watch out!
-Sorry, godfather.

597
00:51:30,862 --> 00:51:33,660
Godfather, my ass.
Did I baptize your kids?

598
00:51:33,865 --> 00:51:36,891
-I’m sorry.
-Now beat it.

599
00:51:39,505 --> 00:51:43,498
Blacky, lend me your bike.

600
00:52:06,965 --> 00:52:09,230
Hey, wanna race?

601
00:52:09,434 --> 00:52:12,893
-Where to?
-Up to the highway.

602
00:52:13,505 --> 00:52:16,440
-Okay.
-Ready? Go!

603
00:52:38,831 --> 00:52:42,664
-Pretty tough, wasn’t it?
-Yeah, you’re good.

604
00:52:42,869 --> 00:52:45,201
Where’d you buy those sneakers?

605
00:52:45,403 --> 00:52:47,998
-Not far from here.
-The shirt, as well?

606
00:52:48,206 --> 00:52:50,538
-No, uptown.
-Cool.

607
00:52:50,742 --> 00:52:52,972
It’s a designer shirt.

608
00:52:53,179 --> 00:52:55,510
If I give you money
can you buy me one?

609
00:52:55,715 --> 00:52:58,376
Shorts and a shirt?

610
00:53:00,619 --> 00:53:02,917
Buy whatever you can.

611
00:53:05,590 --> 00:53:07,650
-What size are you?
-Measure me.

612
00:53:07,860 --> 00:53:10,795
-With what, man?
-Shit, with your hand.

613
00:53:12,297 --> 00:53:15,027
Shoe size? Turn around.

614
00:53:23,809 --> 00:53:28,769
-Hey, Benny!
-You got the digs?

615
00:53:31,784 --> 00:53:35,048
-Just one pair of pants?
-No, there’s more.

616
00:53:40,193 --> 00:53:41,455
-You like it?
-Yeah.

617
00:53:42,728 --> 00:53:45,059
There’s some change.

618
00:53:45,630 --> 00:53:48,565
-Keep it.
-Cool.

619
00:53:57,076 --> 00:53:59,670
This is Benny.

620
00:54:00,780 --> 00:54:04,375
-This is Rocket.
-Hi. I know him.

621
00:54:28,840 --> 00:54:31,502
I’ve become a playboy.

622
00:54:33,445 --> 00:54:37,576
Hey, gangsters, listen to this...

623
00:54:37,782 --> 00:54:39,614
Watch out...

624
00:54:39,818 --> 00:54:43,481
Groovies shake their asses
before laying a big one.

625
00:54:46,958 --> 00:54:48,687
Oh, yeah?

626
00:54:49,561 --> 00:54:52,257
Fuck off, you bastards!

627
00:54:54,599 --> 00:54:58,400
Making fun of me?

628
00:54:59,672 --> 00:55:01,867
Asshole!

629
00:55:16,789 --> 00:55:20,987
Benny, didn’t I tell you to shoot Carrot?
He’s endangering the ghetto.

630
00:55:21,193 --> 00:55:24,720
-Cool it. Go talk to him.
-I’m gonna kill that fucker.

631
00:55:24,931 --> 00:55:27,798
-Stop trying to wipe out everyone.
-I’m gonna kill him.

632
00:55:30,135 --> 00:55:33,128
Don’t worry, Angelica.
The guys in here are cool.

633
00:55:33,338 --> 00:55:35,932
Sure, I’m not worried.

634
00:55:36,409 --> 00:55:40,242
You gonna dance, Benny?
What about Carrot?

635
00:55:40,445 --> 00:55:44,507
Go on, buddy. Go talk to the guy.

636
00:55:44,717 --> 00:55:48,278
Benny was the coolest hood
in the City of God.

637
00:55:48,487 --> 00:55:51,650
He gave away pot,
paid for drinks.

638
00:55:52,157 --> 00:55:55,251
Li’l Z' was the opposite.
He had one obsession:

639
00:55:55,460 --> 00:55:57,428
to be the boss of the ghetto.

640
00:55:57,630 --> 00:56:00,894
He wanted an excuse to take over
Carrot's racket.

641
00:56:01,099 --> 00:56:02,726
-Hey, Carrot.
-What’s up?

642
00:56:02,934 --> 00:56:07,235
You shouldn’t let the Runts
do hold-ups in the ghetto.

643
00:56:07,806 --> 00:56:10,604
You look after your section,
I’ll look after mine.

644
00:56:10,809 --> 00:56:14,677
Got that? I'm gonna get a drink.

645
00:56:22,554 --> 00:56:27,457
-Hey, Rocket! How’s it going?
-Great.

646
00:56:27,659 --> 00:56:30,719
-Hey, Benny!
-How’s it going?

647
00:56:31,496 --> 00:56:34,465
-Hey, Thiago. How are you?
-Good.

648
00:56:35,534 --> 00:56:37,001
-May I?
-Sure...

649
00:56:37,202 --> 00:56:39,500
Wanna dance?

650
00:56:43,009 --> 00:56:46,467
-Is it okay at your place?
-No problem.

651
00:56:46,679 --> 00:56:50,342
My parents are out.
You’ll be all alone with her.

652
00:56:50,548 --> 00:56:54,951
-You can lose your virginity tonight.
-Not so loud, man!

653
00:56:55,153 --> 00:56:56,882
Everyone will hear.

654
00:56:58,123 --> 00:57:00,523
-You’re beautiful.
-Thank you.

655
00:57:00,726 --> 00:57:05,186
-Shit!
-Nothing’s happening.

656
00:57:12,405 --> 00:57:16,705
Look, man, I know the Runts
are associated with you.

657
00:57:16,909 --> 00:57:20,572
Think I'm a sucker, you little brat?
You want to take my racket?

658
00:57:20,780 --> 00:57:24,978
I want to talk to you
because you’re fucking useless.

659
00:57:25,184 --> 00:57:26,173
Get your hand away!

660
00:57:26,385 --> 00:57:29,411
The Runts are screwing up
our security, man.

661
00:57:29,621 --> 00:57:30,952
Give the baby his bottle.

662
00:57:31,157 --> 00:57:33,557
Carrot, just ask the kids
to cool it, okay?

663
00:57:33,759 --> 00:57:37,159
Carrot’s useless. He lets the Runts
do hold-ups in his section.

664
00:57:37,362 --> 00:57:40,297
The police come around and
that’s bad for business.

665
00:57:40,565 --> 00:57:44,160
I’ll do it only because
I like you.

666
00:57:44,503 --> 00:57:46,164
But you need to change
that baby's diapers.

667
00:57:46,371 --> 00:57:50,205
I’ll show you who’s the baby...

668
00:57:50,409 --> 00:57:55,903
Tell the kids that in my ghetto
no one robs or rapes!

669
00:57:56,114 --> 00:57:57,581
No wonder you’re "Little" Z’!

670
00:58:00,753 --> 00:58:05,690
The Runts were kids who didn't
respect the laws of the ghetto.

671
00:58:05,891 --> 00:58:09,349
They would mug residents,
hold up bakeries...

672
00:58:09,561 --> 00:58:11,757
especially in Carrot's section.

673
00:58:14,699 --> 00:58:18,260
What are you doing?

674
00:58:20,039 --> 00:58:24,533
-You rob me all the time!
-But they didn't know...

675
00:58:24,742 --> 00:58:27,074
that the City had a boss now.

676
00:58:28,947 --> 00:58:30,972
THANK YOU FOR CHOOSING US

677
00:58:31,182 --> 00:58:35,016
The City had become
much safer for residents.

678
00:58:36,355 --> 00:58:39,222
There were hardly
any hold-ups now.

679
00:58:39,458 --> 00:58:40,755
You just had to go see Li’l Z'.

680
00:58:40,960 --> 00:58:44,088
-Let’s go.
-Don’t hurt the Runts.

681
00:58:44,295 --> 00:58:47,196
I won’t touch them.

682
00:58:50,869 --> 00:58:52,837
-Hi, Steak.
-How’s it going, Li’l Z’?

683
00:58:53,038 --> 00:58:55,733
-Wanna take a walk, Steak?
-With you? Hold on...

684
00:58:58,177 --> 00:59:01,169
Mom, I’m going out with
my friends.

685
00:59:13,626 --> 00:59:16,288
That’s the best chicken
I ever ate.

686
00:59:16,762 --> 00:59:20,823
-The old guy was scared shitless.
-Feeling sorry for him?

687
00:59:21,032 --> 00:59:24,058
You’re crazy, man!

688
00:59:32,478 --> 00:59:35,345
Why not stick up
a bank or a supermarket?

689
00:59:35,547 --> 00:59:39,984
-Peanuts. Drugs are where it’s at.
-Yeah, selling drugs.

690
00:59:40,186 --> 00:59:46,489
But you have to start out as a delivery
boy. You wanna be a delivery boy?

691
00:59:46,692 --> 00:59:51,925
It’s a rip off.
It takes a long time to move up.

692
00:59:52,231 --> 00:59:56,565
You have to wait till an older guy
gets killed to move up.

693
00:59:56,802 --> 00:59:59,965
I don't wanna wait till some guy
croaks. I'm gonna do what Li’l Z' did.

694
01:00:00,172 --> 01:00:02,867
I'm gonna wipe them all out.

695
01:00:03,074 --> 01:00:05,907
Talking about me, kid?
The boss is here.

696
01:00:10,014 --> 01:00:11,572
Come back, you brat!

697
01:00:15,954 --> 01:00:22,621
-They’re quick, those kids.
-They run fast.

698
01:00:23,862 --> 01:00:26,762
They’re all gone except you.
Any others?

699
01:00:34,340 --> 01:00:37,001
You’re gonna pay
for the ones that escaped.

700
01:00:37,208 --> 01:00:41,373
You choose. Shall I shoot you
in the hand or foot?

701
01:00:41,981 --> 01:00:43,881
Come on, choose!

702
01:00:44,083 --> 01:00:46,847
Hand or foot?

703
01:00:49,387 --> 01:00:52,117
Choose, for fuck's sake!

704
01:00:59,864 --> 01:01:02,992
-Hand.
-The little hand, eh?

705
01:01:11,876 --> 01:01:13,969
Cool.

706
01:01:15,246 --> 01:01:19,649
