01:25:01,470 --> 01:25:03,461
Let’s go!

941
01:25:27,197 --> 01:25:31,132
Gerson...

942
01:25:31,333 --> 01:25:34,929
That bastard killed my brother.

943
01:25:42,878 --> 01:25:45,643
I can’t let that go.

944
01:26:00,863 --> 01:26:02,990
-Want a gun?
-My son...

945
01:26:03,198 --> 01:26:06,599
Calm down, mom.

946
01:26:07,436 --> 01:26:10,304
Please, mom...

947
01:26:19,114 --> 01:26:22,777
Do it right, asshole.

948
01:26:22,985 --> 01:26:26,716
-There’s no other way.
-How’d I let that loser hit me?

949
01:26:26,922 --> 01:26:29,390
Shit, that’s some hole.

950
01:26:59,122 --> 01:27:02,114
-It’s as if we were brothers.
-Shut up.

951
01:27:02,324 --> 01:27:06,853
Both of us hurt in the arm.
You by one brother, me the other.

952
01:27:07,063 --> 01:27:10,863
It would be really funny
if we were brothers.

953
01:27:11,067 --> 01:27:17,164
That Knockout Ned's not bad, eh?
He came out of nowhere.

954
01:27:17,940 --> 01:27:21,569
Shut up, Tuba!
You're a fucking pain!

955
01:27:29,118 --> 01:27:33,282
It was as if the City of God
had suddenly found a hero.

956
01:27:33,489 --> 01:27:35,650
God bless you, son.

957
01:27:35,859 --> 01:27:39,124
That kid was just asking
to be killed.

958
01:27:39,328 --> 01:27:42,024
Well done.

959
01:27:42,231 --> 01:27:45,462
You did a good job.

960
01:27:45,667 --> 01:27:49,296
You’d better go hide.

961
01:27:51,908 --> 01:27:55,173
I thought Knockout Ned
would start a revolution here.

962
01:27:55,377 --> 01:27:58,141
But God had other plans.

963
01:27:58,448 --> 01:28:02,043
Steak,
where are all the dealers?

964
01:28:02,252 --> 01:28:05,517
They’re hiding.
Li’l Z’ is in a bad mood.

965
01:28:05,721 --> 01:28:09,452
They get us hooked and then
they go off and hide.

966
01:28:09,658 --> 01:28:12,889
Do me a favor. Go get some
nose candy for me.

967
01:28:13,095 --> 01:28:14,494
I’ll try.

968
01:28:14,697 --> 01:28:18,154
Tell them it’s for Thiago,
to keep my buzz going.

969
01:28:38,753 --> 01:28:44,123
Steak’n’fries,
go to Carrot’s and tell him...

970
01:28:44,326 --> 01:28:49,695
Li’l Z' says that if you kill
Knockout, he’ll leave you alone.

971
01:28:50,332 --> 01:28:53,199
Hey, Knockout Ned.
Did you hear that?

972
01:28:53,402 --> 01:28:56,064
Grab the kid!

973
01:28:58,239 --> 01:29:03,905
You heard the boy? If you don't
stick with us, you're dead.

974
01:29:04,113 --> 01:29:07,378
I think you should join us.
We'll be partners.

975
01:29:08,050 --> 01:29:10,985
Drugs aren't my thing.

976
01:29:11,186 --> 01:29:13,314
This is just something
between me and him.

977
01:29:13,521 --> 01:29:18,185
Those guys aren’t worth shit.

978
01:29:18,394 --> 01:29:21,989
They'll do anything for power.

979
01:29:22,198 --> 01:29:24,530
Like that kid.

980
01:29:24,733 --> 01:29:28,863
They're all robots,
like this punk here.

981
01:29:29,070 --> 01:29:31,335
What’s in your head, kid?

982
01:29:31,539 --> 01:29:33,974
Can't you see you're
wrecking your life...

983
01:29:34,176 --> 01:29:38,408
with that maniac and a bunch
of trigger-happy fools?

984
01:29:39,881 --> 01:29:46,548
-Are you crazy? You’re just a kid.
-A kid? I smoke, snort...

985
01:29:46,755 --> 01:29:50,054
I’ve killed and robbed.
I’m a man.

986
01:29:50,259 --> 01:29:52,783
Shit, you have no idea!

987
01:29:52,994 --> 01:29:56,225
He’s attached to his gang.
You should join up with us.

988
01:29:56,431 --> 01:30:01,300
-Shall we kill him?
-Steak, we're going to grind you.

989
01:30:02,904 --> 01:30:07,136
-Okay, I accept.
-Great!

990
01:30:07,342 --> 01:30:11,438
Tell your boss that Knockout Ned
and Carrot are now in command.

991
01:30:11,646 --> 01:30:17,846
But on one condition:
no killing of innocent people.

992
01:30:19,488 --> 01:30:22,082
I can't accept that, understand?

993
01:30:22,291 --> 01:30:26,954
Okay, no innocent people.

994
01:30:28,363 --> 01:30:33,300
Steak fucked up!

995
01:30:44,979 --> 01:30:47,573
-Have you a gun for me?
-No...

996
01:30:47,783 --> 01:30:51,184
but we can hold up
a gun store.

997
01:30:51,386 --> 01:30:53,445
That’s no problem.

998
01:30:53,655 --> 01:30:57,251
I don’t want to hold up anything.
I’m not a hoodlum.

999
01:30:57,458 --> 01:31:00,655
This is a personal affair
between me and him, okay?

1000
01:31:01,329 --> 01:31:03,594
I’m not a hoodlum.

1001
01:31:05,967 --> 01:31:07,935
He raped your chick...

1002
01:31:08,136 --> 01:31:11,970
killed your uncle and brother,
gunned your house...

1003
01:31:12,173 --> 01:31:15,541
and you killed one of his guys.

1004
01:31:19,881 --> 01:31:23,510
If you’re not a hood,
then get out.

1005
01:31:28,590 --> 01:31:33,027
THE STORY OF KNOCKOUT NED

1006
01:31:34,194 --> 01:31:36,685
This is a hold-up!

1007
01:31:44,738 --> 01:31:48,367
-The first time...
-Where are the revolvers?

1008
01:31:48,576 --> 01:31:52,204
...Knockout Ned saved a salesclerk
from being shot by Carrot.

1009
01:31:52,412 --> 01:31:56,815
We said no killing!

1010
01:31:57,018 --> 01:31:58,814
That’s the rule.

1011
01:32:00,054 --> 01:32:05,287
We want the boss’ money. Everyone
keep calm. Open the cash register!

1012
01:32:05,493 --> 01:32:08,394
You want us to go?
We do too.

1013
01:32:08,595 --> 01:32:11,029
So hurry up!

1014
01:32:12,266 --> 01:32:14,666
-Look at the ground!
-The second time...

1015
01:32:14,868 --> 01:32:16,802
Carrot saved
Knockout Ned's life.

1016
01:32:19,573 --> 01:32:22,701
Ned learned that there's
an exception to every rule.

1017
01:32:23,344 --> 01:32:25,676
Exception to the rule.

1018
01:32:25,880 --> 01:32:28,974
-Are you the manager?
-Yes.

1019
01:32:29,182 --> 01:32:33,176
This is a hold-up.
Everyone on the ground!

1020
01:32:33,387 --> 01:32:35,412
On the ground!

1021
01:32:35,622 --> 01:32:39,854
Give me the money!

1022
01:32:42,796 --> 01:32:45,026
I’m not kidding.

1023
01:32:45,233 --> 01:32:47,462
The first person who moves
is dead!

1024
01:32:47,868 --> 01:32:51,497
The third time, the exception
becomes the rule.

1025
01:33:07,287 --> 01:33:11,656
Carrot and Knockout Ned
prepared to face Li’l Z'.

1026
01:33:11,859 --> 01:33:14,657
Carrot could protect his
business.

1027
01:33:14,929 --> 01:33:16,692
Knockout Ned...

1028
01:33:16,898 --> 01:33:19,833
the best marksman in his battalion,
wanted revenge.

1029
01:33:20,033 --> 01:33:24,231
First, the Italians.
This is a 9 mm.

1030
01:33:24,972 --> 01:33:27,202
-Let me see.
-Not bad, eh?

1031
01:33:27,408 --> 01:33:32,106
-The sight isn’t well-aligned.
-I’ll give you a good price.

1032
01:33:32,913 --> 01:33:34,904
The 12 mm, the "hand job".

1033
01:33:35,550 --> 01:33:36,778
See why?

1034
01:33:36,984 --> 01:33:40,045
An Uzi, 9 mm. It’s Israeli.

1035
01:33:40,253 --> 01:33:43,121
-The star of David.
-Jewish.

1036
01:33:43,323 --> 01:33:44,688
I want a 30-06.

1037
01:33:45,158 --> 01:33:47,524
Now we can start having fun.

1038
01:33:47,729 --> 01:33:52,063
The war’s on.
Let’s start with a prayer.

1039
01:33:52,432 --> 01:33:56,528
Our Father who art in heaven
hallowed be our name...

1040
01:33:56,738 --> 01:34:00,902
Our will be done...

1041
01:34:01,442 --> 01:34:03,932
On earth as it is in heaven...

1042
01:34:17,190 --> 01:34:19,250
Hoodlums have guns,
but can't shoot.

1043
01:34:19,560 --> 01:34:23,587
One bullet from Knockout Ned
was worth ten from Li’l Z”s gang.

1044
01:34:23,797 --> 01:34:27,927
Li’l Z' couldn't take it.
He counter-attacked.

1045
01:34:30,570 --> 01:34:34,802
The ghetto had been a purgatory,
now it was hell.

1046
01:34:38,746 --> 01:34:44,445
I decided to get out.
That's how I became a reporter.

1047
01:34:45,319 --> 01:34:47,753
Great photo!

1048
01:34:47,954 --> 01:34:50,422
I bet it’s by Rogerio Reis.

1049
01:34:50,992 --> 01:34:53,824
What did I tell you?

1050
01:34:54,028 --> 01:34:56,222
Like any pro...

1051
01:34:56,430 --> 01:34:59,866
I started at the bottom,
way down at the bottom.

1052
01:35:00,068 --> 01:35:03,525
Without knowing what awaited me.

1053
01:35:05,172 --> 01:35:08,141
Instead of going home
I’d go over to the paper.

1054
01:35:08,341 --> 01:35:11,708
A guy from the City of God
worked in the lab.

1055
01:35:11,912 --> 01:35:14,779
Check this out.

1056
01:35:14,981 --> 01:35:19,042
He helped me move closer to
what I loved most in life.

1057
01:35:19,252 --> 01:35:20,880
-Hi, Rogerio.
-How are you, Pierre?

1058
01:35:21,088 --> 01:35:23,716
This is Rocket.
He’s a photographer.

1059
01:35:23,925 --> 01:35:25,085
Hello, Rocket.

1060
01:35:25,292 --> 01:35:27,556
-He’s a fan of yours.
-Really?

1061
01:35:27,761 --> 01:35:29,389
You have good taste, Rocket!

1062
01:35:29,596 --> 01:35:32,690
-Well, I’m done. I’m off.
-See you.

1063
01:35:32,899 --> 01:35:35,561
What a cool guy!

1064
01:35:36,369 --> 01:35:39,463
What should have been
a swift revenge...

1065
01:35:39,673 --> 01:35:42,164
turned into an all-out war.

1066
01:35:47,280 --> 01:35:49,510
The City of God was divided.

1067
01:35:49,716 --> 01:35:53,516
You couldn't go from one
section to the other.

1068
01:35:53,720 --> 01:35:55,950
Not even to visit a relative.

1069
01:35:56,157 --> 01:35:59,887
The cops considered anyone
living in the ghetto a hoodlum.

1070
01:36:00,094 --> 01:36:03,529
People got used to living
in Vietnam.

1071
01:36:07,734 --> 01:36:12,694
And more and more volunteers
kept signing up to die.

1072
01:36:12,907 --> 01:36:13,895
This kid...

1073
01:36:14,108 --> 01:36:16,837
-What do you want?
-A boy from Carrot’s gang punched me.

1074
01:36:17,377 --> 01:36:18,742
The war was
an excuse for everything.

1075
01:36:19,146 --> 01:36:21,114
One of Li’l Z”s soldiers
kicked me.

1076
01:36:23,150 --> 01:36:25,175
Take this .22.

1077
01:36:26,988 --> 01:36:29,456
The jerk who raped my sister is
with Carrot.

1078
01:36:29,657 --> 01:36:31,056
Li’l Z’ evicted my family.

1079
01:36:32,092 --> 01:36:33,720
Kill... Be respected.

1080
01:36:46,106 --> 01:36:51,568
-I’m Thiago, a friend of Benny’s.
-Can you read? Can you add?

1081
01:36:51,779 --> 01:36:57,217
-I’m pretty good in business.
-Okay, get to work.

1082
01:36:57,717 --> 01:37:01,085
-What do you want?
-To get my father’s murderer.

1083
01:37:01,488 --> 01:37:04,252
-What’s your name?
-My name’s Otto.

1084
01:37:09,697 --> 01:37:11,664
What’s the matter?

1085
01:37:11,865 --> 01:37:15,824
-He’s a worker.
-But he wants a gun.

1086
01:37:16,570 --> 01:37:19,233
He won’t last a week.

1087
01:37:30,251 --> 01:37:35,086
A year later, no one
remembered how it had all begun.

1088
01:37:35,288 --> 01:37:36,619
Take that!

1089
01:37:39,426 --> 01:37:45,365
For both sides, the aim was to take
over the enemy's business in order...

1090
01:37:45,565 --> 01:37:49,092
to buy more guns and take over
more businesses.

1091
01:38:10,925 --> 01:38:14,122
I smoke, snort,
I’ve killed and robbed.

1092
01:38:14,328 --> 01:38:16,660
I’m a man.

1093
01:38:38,319 --> 01:38:43,347
The media started taking an interest.
The police had to intervene.

1094
01:38:57,305 --> 01:39:01,708
A gang leader, from the City of God,
was arrested today.

1095
01:39:01,908 --> 01:39:03,637
Manuel Machado,
a.k.a. Knockout Ned...

1096
01:39:03,844 --> 01:39:07,244
was hospitalized after being
wounded by Li’l Z”s gang.

1097
01:39:07,448 --> 01:39:09,677
Our reporter interviewed him.

1098
01:39:09,884 --> 01:39:13,842
-Is the war still going on?
-It's still going on.

1099
01:39:14,121 --> 01:39:18,649
-Have many people died?
-Many have died.

1100
01:39:18,859 --> 01:39:20,986
Mostly innocent people.

1101
01:39:21,194 --> 01:39:24,561
Just knowing me is enough...

1102
01:39:24,765 --> 01:39:29,498
to get you killed by Li’l Z'.

1103
01:39:29,703 --> 01:39:33,070
-The police don’t go in there?
-They go after me, not him.

1104
01:39:33,274 --> 01:39:39,611
I’ve been in jail, while he goes
on killing undisturbed.

1105
01:39:39,814 --> 01:39:41,907
And they don’t arrest him.

1106
01:39:42,115 --> 01:39:44,413
Knockout Ned says
the war will continue.

1107
01:39:44,618 --> 01:39:50,215
Police Chief Guedes has promised
to arrest both of the gangs.

1108
01:39:58,698 --> 01:40:00,427
Motherfucker!

1109
01:40:00,634 --> 01:40:04,194
I’m the boss here, but he gets
his picture in the paper!

1110
01:40:04,404 --> 01:40:07,965
-Have you found mine?
-Just Knockout Ned’s.

1111
01:40:08,175 --> 01:40:09,641
Keep looking.

1112
01:40:10,043 --> 01:40:12,773
At least my name’s
got to be in there.

1113
01:40:12,979 --> 01:40:14,674
-There’s nothing.
-Can you read?

1114
01:40:14,881 --> 01:40:17,315
Just the pictures.

1115
01:40:18,284 --> 01:40:20,344
Nothing.

1116
01:40:20,554 --> 01:40:23,648
Hey, what the fuck are you doing?

1117
01:40:23,858 --> 01:40:28,989
-It’s just the want ads.
-I don’t care, read everything!

1118
01:40:29,195 --> 01:40:33,359
-But there aren’t any articles.
-Want a bullet in your head?

1119
01:40:35,368 --> 01:40:38,860
Gotta show them who’s boss here.

1120
01:40:43,911 --> 01:40:47,608
-Give me the camera!
-No way!

1121
01:40:50,150 --> 01:40:52,483
Take my picture, man.

1122
01:40:53,087 --> 01:40:55,817
I can’t work it.

1123
01:40:56,023 --> 01:40:57,717
Go ahead.

1124
01:40:58,091 --> 01:41:02,653
-I’ll hold the Beretta.
-Let me try...

1125
01:41:03,296 --> 01:41:05,992
Back off...

1126
01:41:06,199 --> 01:41:10,465
-There’s no click.
-What a bunch of bozos!

1127
01:41:10,970 --> 01:41:13,734
I’m fucked with you guys.

1128
01:41:15,810 --> 01:41:18,370
I have an idea.

1129
01:41:18,578 --> 01:41:23,106
I’ll go get a guy I know.
Hang loose.

1130
01:41:23,984 --> 01:41:27,886
-Here he is.
-Take the camera.

1131
01:41:28,588 --> 01:41:31,023
Well, kid?

1132
01:41:32,091 --> 01:41:37,496
Aren’t you a photographer?
Make the camerawork. We can’t do it.

1133
01:41:39,300 --> 01:41:41,096
Take our picture.

1134
01:41:46,039 --> 01:41:49,840
-You fucking broke it.
-It wasn’t me.

1135
01:41:50,411 --> 01:41:52,105
I found it.

1136
01:41:53,948 --> 01:41:56,109
It has to be wound.

1137
01:42:00,554 --> 01:42:03,546
-What’s your name?
-Rocket.

1138
01:42:03,923 --> 01:42:07,859
-Another picture, Rocket.
-How about two rows?

1139
01:42:08,061 --> 01:42:12,965
-What?
-Two rows. Everyone with their guns.

1140
01:42:13,734 --> 01:42:17,761
-You’re outside, for Christ’s sake!
-Talk to him nicely, kid.

1141
01:42:17,971 --> 01:42:19,905
Sorry. Move in, please.

1142
01:42:22,408 --> 01:42:24,876
Another one.

1143
01:42:29,250 --> 01:42:31,547
-I think the roll’s finished.
-Then show us the pictures.

1144
01:42:31,752 --> 01:42:34,619
-They have to be developed.
-Developed?

1145
01:42:35,855 --> 01:42:37,516
How much is it?

1146
01:42:38,125 --> 01:42:42,528
Take this money.
And bring back the pictures.

1147
01:42:42,729 --> 01:42:47,996
-I have to remove the film.
-Keep the camera.

1148
01:42:48,502 --> 01:42:52,905
Benny wanted to give it to you,
didn’t he? So, it’s yours...

1149
01:42:53,106 --> 01:42:54,938
Thanks.

1150
01:42:56,877 --> 01:43:01,075
Don’t forget the pictures.
The photos, Rocket!

1151
01:43:12,158 --> 01:43:14,490
-Pierre!
-What?

1152
01:43:14,895 --> 01:43:18,262
Can you develop this for me?

1153
01:43:18,966 --> 01:43:22,423
I can’t, Rocket.
I could get into trouble.

1154
01:43:22,636 --> 01:43:25,365
It’s only for the paper’s reporters.
I could risk my job.

1155
01:43:25,573 --> 01:43:27,063
-Pierre?
-Yes, Rogerio?

1156
01:43:27,274 --> 01:43:31,904
Develop these for me.
This one too, okay?

1157
01:43:32,313 --> 01:43:34,679
I’m going to lunch.

1158
01:43:34,881 --> 01:43:38,977
You’re lucky. What size?

1159
01:43:39,185 --> 01:43:42,586
-What?
-For the enlargement, what size?

1160
01:43:43,056 --> 01:43:46,856
Well... Whatever you think is best.

1161
01:44:06,646 --> 01:44:08,774
-Here.
-Thanks.

1162
01:44:12,653 --> 01:44:15,315
I’m in deep shit now.

1163
01:44:17,224 --> 01:44:19,748
I’m as good as dead.

1164
01:44:31,005 --> 01:44:33,097
Someone had signed
my death sentence.

1165
01:44:33,306 --> 01:44:36,764
I wanted to bash the jerk's face in.

1166
01:44:42,448 --> 01:44:46,077
Are you Marina?
Because of you I’m dead.

1167
01:44:46,286 --> 01:44:48,413
You stole my photos.

1168
01:44:48,622 --> 01:44:52,490
Dead? Stole? What do you mean?
Not so loud.

1169
01:44:53,793 --> 01:44:56,318
Not so loud?
I’ll be killed because of you.

1170
01:44:56,529 --> 01:44:59,090
You were gone,
your photos were in the lab.

1171
01:44:59,298 --> 01:45:02,131
There's nothing I can do.
The photos in our lab...

1172
01:45:02,336 --> 01:45:05,134
are photos to be published
in the paper.

1173
01:45:05,338 --> 01:45:08,604
I saw the photos,
I published them.

1174
01:45:08,809 --> 01:45:11,208
-You stole them.
-I did not. Here they are.

1175
01:45:11,412 --> 01:45:15,780
-Give them to me.
-Just a second.

1176
01:45:15,983 --> 01:45:19,110
Here are your photos.

1177
01:45:19,319 --> 01:45:23,085
-Are there any others?
